      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">Strontium is a silvery-white metal, soft and lustrous. Its ions impart a red colour to a flame. Due to its high reactivity, strontium has to be stored in kerosene. It loses its lustre on exposure to air, becoming covered in a yellow coating of the products of reaction with oxygen and nitrogen - strontium oxide - SrO and strontium nitride  – S</text>
