      </subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">. A radioactive isotope of strontium,</text>
      <subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="13" fc="0" fa="1" charset="238"></text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">90</text>
      </subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">Sr, </text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">a product of nuclear fission, is a radioactive poison, accumulating in bone marrow. The element was named after the Scottish town of Strontian, where strontium minerals were found at the end of the 18th century. Strontium was first obtained by the English chemist Humphry Davy in 1808.</text>
